article.description: Marshall Henderson scored 24 points to lead Utah past TCU on Wednesday.
article.headline: Henderson's 24 points help Utah to hold off TCU
article.linkText: Henderson's 24 points help Utah to hold off TCU
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Marshall Henderson scored 24 points to lead Utah to a 64-55 victory over TCU Wednesday night. Carlon Brown added 13 points for the Utes (11-12, 4-5 Mountain West). Henderson, who played just 25 minutes, scored Utah's first eight points and had 14 in the first half as the Utes took a 32-29 lead. His 3-pointer with 6:46 put Utah ahead to stay at 46-43. In the final two minutes, Henderson and Luka Drca combined to go 10-for-10 from the free-throw line to put the game out of reach. Drca finished with nine points. Nikola Cerina led the Horned Frogs (11-14, 3-7) with 17 points. Ronnie Moss added 12. TCU was 8-for-29 (28 percent) from the field in the second half. Utah was 16-for-18 from the free-throw line and TCU was 14-for-15.
